file: bmptk/examples/graphics/README

Bare Metal Programming Tool Kit eaxmples/graphics directory

This directory contains exaples that use the bmptk graphics library.
Most examples can be used with any target that supports a
graphics screen, like win, nds, or a microcontroller with an LCD deisplay.

This directory contains :
   Makefile : supports 'clean' and 'build' targets
   README   : this file

subdirectories
   align         : shows the effect of various text alignments
   clocks        : draws clocks, demonstrating various frame decorators
   draw          : draw text, lines, boxes, circles, pictures, etc.
   export        : draw a still clock and export it to a bmp file (win only)
   lines         : draws random lines
  







